article.headline: Centenary 47, W. Illinois 45
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. -- Chase Adams scored 13 points to lead Centenary to a 47-45 win over Western Illinois on Thursday. David Perez added 10 points for Centenary (4-14, 2-4 Summit), which withstood a furious second-half rally by Western Illinois (6-11, 3-3). Centenary led 28-16 at the half, holding the Leathernecks to 23 percent from the field on 5-of-22 shooting. But Western Illinois stormed back after the break, going on a 9-2 run to start the second half. Tommie Tyler's free throw tied the game at 34 with 9:51 left. The teams traded the lead until a layup by Nick Stallings with 6:35 left put Centenary up for good. Lance Hill's layup with 2:21 left and a free throw by Adams with 10 seconds left kept the game out of reach. David Dubois led Western Illinois with 14 points. Quenton Kirby added 12 points.
